            <span class="utterance" who="tcharnabrodaR" start="1332.340" end="x">And then a few days later, we would go as a working crew to that place, and carried the ashes into the fields. The fields of <a class="placename" href="#vothC69" type="camp">Majdanek</a> are now fructiferous, from the ashes of the burned people, Now then . . . these selections were insufficient. They had to present us with another spectacle, and that was the hanging in <a class="placename" href="#vothC69" type="camp">Majdanek</a>. It was supposedly as punishment for escape, allegedly some had attempted to escape. That was also not true. Because it was impossible to imagine that such a thing could be attempted there.</span>
